caption: An essential space to breathe in Paris, off the tourist train. If you have walked the High Line in New York City this is a similar wander across a beautiful landscape, surrounded by architecture and nature.  Only problem was knowing when it ended! Not clearly signposted at one end so simply gave up as there were several directions to follow and none signposted!

Beautiful area to jogging around the Paris city You can also enjoy the view of the bridge Near Gare du Lyon metro station and close to many shops. Under the bridge you can also visit so many art shops and stores, and restaurants.

AKA the 'Paris Highline' this raised pathwalk allows you to levitate among the trees and breathe through the city almost as free as a bird. Joggers, couples, casual strollers - all find their way seamlessly through this green artery. Don't make plans for later, there's no reason to.

Enter here the enchanted world of Promenade Plant√©e, the older brother of the NYC High Line that will serve for an amazing 5km walk. Above the rustle and bustle of busy Paris, all the way to the  Vincennes Wood. Magical! P.S. Jogging in the park is allowed only as long as it‚Äôs not obtrusive to others.
Fabulous quiet and leafy walking path in the midst of all the Paris hubub! Enjoyable.

The Viaduc de la Bastille is 1,5 km long and consists of 64 vaults. Its purpose was to support an elevated train line from 1859 to 1969. In 1998, the viaduc was converted into a strip of workshops and caf√©s occupying the vaults closed for this purpose. It now goes by the name of Viaduc des Arts.
Wonderful peaceful place with imaginative planting, intimate views of fascinating domestic architecture. Lucky Parisians, living around here. O
Good to pass a few minutes while waiting for a train
A unique park, that offers you a new perspective :)

Aaaah, I love paying a visit to this neighborhood for our Paris trips. The shops are fun to watch the artists at work and afterwards we walk back through the lusciously green promenade plant√©e. A hearty recommendation!
What a wonderful walk to enjoy views of a beautiful city and relax in a peaceful setting!
Great place to walk and get to know paris from above
A lovely elevated linear garden.  Beautiful in April.  Well worth a visit for a quiet stroll with great views. Feels far removed from the hustle and bustle below.
My favourite place in Paris. The street itself is interesting if you are an artist. The lady there is very friendly and helpful if you like fabric you can spend hours and hours there.
Amazing little Oasis in the middle of the city

Suggest you spend a morning walking along the Promenade des Plantes then back along the viaduct... amazing hoteliers, galleries & shops. If doors locked, just ring bell and you'll be made most welcome.
Beautiful walk above street level!
Genius idea full of of parfum of artistic activities with roof garden on top.
Walk in another green world through the middle of Paris
Really fun and interesting. It's right near the train station, so you can waste some time here while waiting for your train. If you're nearby don't miss it.
Very pretty place with what inspired the green "Highline" in New York on top and a bunch of cool places on ground level
Except for the green walking path itself, the restaurants and other businesses that line the walk at street level are too trendy/artificial/yuppie for my taste.
Super pretty escape above the city. Great for long, calm walks or evening jogs.

A pleasant place to stroll and get a little peace among the hustle and bustle
Lovely place in the centre of the city to get away from it all.
Magnificent, relaxing walk full of romantic scenery.
Green place between buildings. Good spot for rest.
Very nice open air walk in the Center of Paris
Very green, nice flowers, good for a walk
Wonderful place to visit and walk through
Go for a walk, you won't regret it
A must visit for all tourists (and locals!).
